title: Gunmen carry out attack near Jewish settlement in the West Bank | DW News
text: Eight people have been wounded in a shooting attack in the Israeli-occupied West Bank. Israeli police say three gunmen opened fire on civilian cars lined up in a traffic jam. The attackers arrived at the scene in a car with a Palestinian license plate. Two of the gunmen were killed. The incident took place near the entrance to the Maale Adumim settlement, east of Jerusalem.
